What is %msg: ?
_______________
What %msg is
In RAP, %msg is a special component on the failed and reported result structures (and sometimes on mapped results, depending on API version). 
You use it to attach one message instance (T100, message class, or text) to a specific row (identified by %tky / keys),
so the runtime can show it in the UI or log it consistently.

It is not a normal database field; it exists only on these control structures returned from MODIFY, READ, etc.

Where it appears
Context	Role of %msg
failed-<node>	- table containsExplains why an instance failed (validation error, lock, authority, etc.).
reported-<node>	- tables contains Informational or warning messages and error messages returned by the BO logic during process..

%msg - return to ui level.- to pass the %msg message, we need reported parameter.
Together with %tky-	Links the message to the exact business object instance (or key

Typical pattern: you fill %tky (or the key fields, depending on your template) and %msg so the framework knows which row the message belongs to.

How messages are created (conceptually):
_______________________________________
You usually assign %msg an object that implements the RAP message interface (commonly IF_ABAP_BEHV_MESSAGE) — 
for example via cl_abap_behv_message (or cl_abap_behv_message_factory / new_message_with_text-style APIs, depending on release).

CONNCEPTUALLY:

" Pseudocode – pattern only; exact factory/API depends on your release
reported-Travel = VALUE #(
  (
    %tky     = <travel_tky>
    %msg     = cl_abap_behv_message=>create_t100( ... )  " or new_message_with_text( ... )
  )
).

(Exact class/method names and whether you use %tky vs. key fields follow your behavior definition and ABAP release.)
Mental model
Piece	- Meaning
%tky	- Which instance.
%msg	- What to tell the user about that instance.
failed vs reported	- Error/stop vs info/warning (semantics differ; both can carry %msg).

Practical notes:
_________
Prefer T100 or message class messages for translation and consistency; ad-hoc text is possible but weaker for prod.
%msg is about RAP message propagation to the UI/OData layer — it is not a replacement for business logic; you still set failed when the operation must not succeed.
